In the context of [[wireless networking]], '''Constant Awake Mode''' ('''CAM''') is a mode that is intended for devices when power is not an issue, such as when [[AC power]] is available to a device.<ref>https://laird-ews-support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/1430695-power-save-modes-cam-fast-max-?b_id=1982</ref> This mode provides the best connectivity  from the user perspective. CAM is also appropriate when a portable device will be used for only a short time that the [[Battery (electricity)|battery]] can easily accommodate. This is the most commonly used mode, and can be contrasted with power saving modes, which may or may not be offered by a particular device.

