This is an engineering term for describing how far to drive [[Deep foundation|pile]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/library/policy/army/fm/5-134/ch4.pdf|title=Pile Installation|date=8 April 1985|website=www.globalsecurity.org}}</ref>  It is also used in [[surveying]] when driving metal posts and [[monument]]s that usually mark the corners of properties.

A rod or pile has been "driven to refusal" when five more blows of an adequate hammer will not budge the rod or pile.

